(350, 'of_template', 'a:294:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:14:\"Most Important\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:25:\"Real Estate or Car Sales?\";s:4:\"desc\";s:140:\"<strong style=\'color: red;\'>IMOPORTANT: After your choice, please refresh this page before making any more changes in Theme Options</strong>\";s:2:\"id\";s:7:\"wp_site\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:11:\"Real Estate\";i:1;s:9:\"Car Sales\";}s:3:\"std\";s:11:\"Real Estate\";}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:19:\"Search Results Page\";s:4:\"desc\";s:206:\"What \'Page\' is your Search Results. (Note: you must create a \'Page\' for Search Results. Give it a title. Also give it the Page Template name called \'Search Results\'. That page will appear in this dropdown.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:20:\"wp_searchresultspage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:10:{i:0;s:14:\"Select a page:\";i:1;s:7:\"Compare\";i:2;s:10:\"Contact Us\";i:3;s:14:\"Meet the Staff\";i:4;s:26:\"Purchase: Lets get started\";i:5;s:11:\"Sample Page\";i:6;s:14:\"Search Results\";i:7;s:8:\"Site Map\";i:8;s:4:\"Sold\";i:9;s:10:\"Thank You!\";}s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Print Page\";s:4:\"desc\";s:295:\"What is your listings \'Print\' page? This is the page that is specially formatted for nice printing output for your listings. (Note: you must create a \'Page\'. Give it a title (anything you like). Also give it the Page Template name called \'Print Listing\'. That page will appear in this dropdown.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_printpage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:10:{i:0;s:14:\"Select a page:\";i:1;s:7:\"Compare\";i:2;s:10:\"Contact Us\";i:3;s:14:\"Meet the Staff\";i:4;s:26:\"Purchase: Lets get started\";i:5;s:11:\"Sample Page\";i:6;s:14:\"Search Results\";i:7;s:8:\"Site Map\";i:8;s:4:\"Sold\";i:9;s:10:\"Thank You!\";}s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Homepage Layouts\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:39:\"What to show under slideshow (1st area)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:162:\"Under the slideshow on the homepage, to the right of the left column search area, are 3 main sections: Recent Listins, 3 widgetized blocks, and Recent Blog posts.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_homepage_layout1\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:3:{i:0;s:15:\"Recent Listings\";i:1;s:7:\"Widgets\";i:2;s:10:\"Blog Posts\";}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:39:\"What to show under slideshow (2nd area)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:162:\"Under the slideshow on the homepage, to the right of the left column search area, are 3 main sections: Recent Listins, 3 widgetized blocks, and Recent Blog posts.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_homepage_layout2\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:7:\"Widgets\";i:1;s:15:\"Recent Listings\";i:2;s:10:\"Blog Posts\";i:3;s:9:\"[nothing]\";}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:39:\"What to show under slideshow (3rd area)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:162:\"Under the slideshow on the homepage, to the right of the left column search area, are 3 main sections: Recent Listins, 3 widgetized blocks, and Recent Blog posts.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_homepage_layout3\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:10:\"Blog Posts\";i:1;s:7:\"Widgets\";i:2;s:15:\"Recent Listings\";i:3;s:9:\"[nothing]\";}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:29:\"Widget layout on the homepage\";s:4:\"desc\";s:297:\"If you opt to show the widgetized area on the homepage, you have 4 layout choices.<br /><br />1. 3 equal size widget areas<br /><br />2. Two widget areas, right one twice as wide as the left.<br /><br />3. Two widget areas, left one  twice as wide as the right.<br /><br />4. One wide widget area.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_widgetlayout\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:8:\"Layout 1\";i:1;s:8:\"Layout 2\";i:2;s:8:\"Layout 3\";i:3;s:8:\"Layout 4\";}}i:9;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Appearance\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:17:\"Main Color Scheme\";s:4:\"desc\";s:346:\"Set the colour scheme for the theme.  This color will be used for the site background, headers, and buttons.  It is best to choose relatively dark colors, otherwise some headers will appear too light against light backgrounds.  If you do choose a very light color, you will have to edit some CSS so some text is legible against light backgrounds.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_color_scheme\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:7:\"#a81c1c\";}i:11;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:46:\"Text color (if main color scheme is too light)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:172:\"If your color scheme (above) is fairly light, then the standard white text that is sometimes on top of it may be hard to read. Choose a darker color here to override white.\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_textcolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:12;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Logo URL (Main)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:106:\"Enter the link to your logo image.  Simply upload image with Wordpress, and copy/paste the final URL here.\";s:2:\"id\";s:7:\"wp_logo\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:13;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Logo width\";s:4:\"desc\";s:301:\"Width of logo area. If you make this more than 300, then the width will cause side scrolling when viewed on small very small mobile devices. So if no side scrolling is important, then try to keep your logo under 300 px wide. If this setting is 300 and your logo is wider, then it will get clipped off.\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_logowidth\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:3:\"300\";}i:14;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Logo position X\";s:4:\"desc\";s:61:\"Tweak the X/Y position of the logo (X is horizontal position)\";s:2:\"id\";s:9:\"wp_logo_x\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"0\";}i:15;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Logo position Y\";s:4:\"desc\";s:109:\"Tweak the X/Y position of the logo (Y is vertical position).  Negative numbers go up, positive numbers, down.\";s:2:\"id\";s:9:\"wp_logo_y\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"0\";}i:16;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:14:\"Secondary Logo\";s:4:\"desc\";s:104:\"Upload optional secondary logo image.  This logo is optional and placed in the right side of the header.\";s:2:\"id\";s:8:\"wp_logo2\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:17;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:19:\"Secondary Logo link\";s:4:\"desc\";s:58:\"URL to link to when you click the optional secondary logo.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_secondarylogourl\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:18;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:13:\"Header height\";s:4:\"desc\";s:103:\"Height of the header area. If your logo is large, you can increase this number to allow for more space.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_headerheight\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:3:\"150\";}i:19;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Background Color\";s:4:\"desc\";s:260:\"The background color is seen to the left and right of the site, with screens wider than 960px. This color can be combined with the next setting, \'Background Image\'. In this case, the color will only show if the image tiling is not filling up the entire screen.\";s:2:\"id\";s:18:\"wp_backgroundcolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:20;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Background Image\";s:4:\"desc\";s:637:\"The background image is seen to the left and right of the sige, with screens wider than 960px.  This image can be combined with the previous setting, \'Background Color\'. The image will overlap any chosen color<br /><br />Tip: this theme doesn\'t include any backgrounds, because there are just too many styles and designs possible. Instead, there are many websites that offer free seamless background images. My favorite is: <a target=_blank  href=\'http://subtlepatterns.com/\'>http://subtlepatterns.com/</a>. Just download, unzip, and upload here.<br ><br />You can use a light or dark color and it will not affect the legibility of text.\";s:2:\"id\";s:18:\"wp_backgroundimage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:21;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:23:\"Background Image Tiling\";s:4:\"desc\";s:67:\"Repeat the background image on the X axis, Y axis, or don\'t repeat.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_backgroundrepeat\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:6:\"repeat\";i:1;s:8:\"repeat-x\";i:2;s:8:\"repeat-y\";i:3;s:9:\"no-repeat\";}s:3:\"std\";s:6:\"repeat\";}i:22;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:19:\"Background Position\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:21:\"wp_backgroundposition\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:9:{i:0;s:8:\"left top\";i:1;s:11:\"left center\";i:2;s:11:\"left bottom\";i:3;s:9:\"right top\";i:4;s:12:\"right center\";i:5;s:12:\"right bottom\";i:6;s:10:\"center top\";i:7;s:13:\"center center\";i:8;s:13:\"center bottom\";}s:3:\"std\";s:8:\"left top\";}i:23;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:21:\"Background Attachment\";s:4:\"desc\";s:78:\"Do you want the background image to scroll along with the page, or stay fixed?\";s:2:\"id\";s:23:\"wp_backgroundattachment\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:5:\"fixed\";i:1;s:6:\"scroll\";}s:3:\"std\";s:5:\"fixed\";}i:24;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Header Color\";s:4:\"desc\";s:498:\"The header color for the site. If no color is chosen, it will default to white. This chosen color will override the optional header background image setting below.<br /><br />Tip: enter \'transparent\' if you want the site background color/background to show here.<br ><br /><strong>Note: </strong>the current theme design expects a light color. If you choose a dark color here, then any text overlapping this area may be hard to read. It will be up to you to edit style.css to change the text color.\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_headercolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:25;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Header Image\";s:4:\"desc\";s:267:\"The header image for the site. <br ><br /<strong>Note: </strong> the current theme design expects a light image. If you choose a dark image here, then any text overlapping this area may be hard to read. It will be up to you to edit style.css to change the text color.\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_headerimage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:26;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:19:\"Header Image Tiling\";s:4:\"desc\";s:63:\"Repeat the header image on the X axis, Y axis, or don\'t repeat.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_headerrepeat\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:8:\"repeat-x\";i:1;s:8:\"repeat-y\";i:2;s:9:\"no-repeat\";i:3;s:6:\"repeat\";}s:3:\"std\";s:8:\"repeat-x\";}i:27;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:27:\"Title area background color\";s:4:\"desc\";s:435:\"The title area for all site pages other than the homepage. It defaults to a dark gray, but you can override the color here. This optional color will override the title background setting below.<br ><br /><strong>Note: </strong> the current theme design expects a dark color here. If you choose a light color here, then any text overlapping this area may be hard to read. It will be up to you to edit style.css to change the text color.\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_titlecolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:28;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:27:\"Title area background image\";s:4:\"desc\";s:374:\"The title area for all site pages other than the homepage. Choose a background image. The color setting above will override this setting.<br ><br /><strong>Note: </strong> the current theme design expects a dark image. If you choose a light color here, then any text overlapping this area may be hard to read. It will be up to you to edit style.css to change the text color.\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_titleimage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:29;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:34:\"Title area background image Tiling\";s:4:\"desc\";s:62:\"Repeat the title image on the X axis, Y axis, or don\'t repeat.\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_titlerepeat\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:6:\"repeat\";i:1;s:8:\"repeat-x\";i:2;s:8:\"repeat-y\";i:3;s:9:\"no-repeat\";}s:3:\"std\";s:6:\"repeat\";}i:30;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:23:\"Footer background color\";s:4:\"desc\";s:421:\"The title area for all site pages other than the homepage. It defaults to a dark gray, but you can override the color here. This color will override the title background setting below.<br ><br /><strong>Note: </strong> the current theme design expects a dark color. If you choose a light color here, then any text overlapping this area may be hard to read. It will be up to you to edit style.css to change the text color.\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_footercolor\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"color\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:31;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:23:\"Footer background image\";s:4:\"desc\";s:374:\"The title area for all site pages other than the homepage. Choose a background image. The color setting above will override this setting.<br ><br /><strong>Note: </strong> the current theme design expects a dark image. If you choose a light color here, then any text overlapping this area may be hard to read. It will be up to you to edit style.css to change the text color.\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_footerimage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"upload\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:32;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:30:\"Footer background image Tiling\";s:4:\"desc\";s:62:\"Repeat the title image on the X axis, Y axis, or don\'t repeat.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_footerrepeat\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:4:{i:0;s:6:\"repeat\";i:1;s:8:\"repeat-x\";i:2;s:8:\"repeat-y\";i:3;s:9:\"no-repeat\";}s:3:\"std\";s:6:\"repeat\";}i:33;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:58:\"Google Font LINK code (For section headings, titles, ect.)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:89:\"Find the desired font on www.google.com/webfonts, then copy the LINK code and paste here.\";s:2:\"id\";s:8:\"wp_font1\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"textarea\";s:3:\"std\";s:92:\"<link href=\'http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Oswald\' rel=\'stylesheet\' type=\'text/css\'>\";}i:34;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:57:\"Google Font CSS code (For section headings, titles, ect.)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:88:\"Find the desired font on www.google.com/webfonts, then copy the CSS code and paste here.\";s:2:\"id\";s:8:\"wp_font2\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:34:\"font-family: \'Oswald\', sans-serif;\";}i:35;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:64:\"Alternate standard web font (for section headings, titles, etc.)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:184:\"If you don\'t want to use Google Web Fonts (see above) then use this standard web font family. Note: Delete the Google Fonts code in the 2 settings above in order for this font to work.\";s:2:\"id\";s:8:\"wp_font3\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:33:\"font-family: \'Arial\', sans-serif;\";}i:36;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:22:\"Listing display layout\";s:4:\"desc\";s:97:\"For Search Results, Browse By page results, and Recent Listings, what type of layout do you want?\";s:2:\"id\";s:16:\"wp_listinglayout\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:18:\"Three per row grid\";i:1;s:11:\"One per row\";}}i:37;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:19:\"Blog display layout\";s:4:\"desc\";s:67:\"For the blog/news page of results, what type of layout do you want?\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_bloglayout\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:2:{i:0;s:11:\"One per row\";i:1;s:18:\"Three per row grid\";}}i:38;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"Custom CSS\";s:4:\"desc\";s:223:\"Want to add any custom CSS code? Put in here, and the rest is taken care of. This overrides any other stylesheets. eg: a.button{color:green}. The CSS is placed in the head of every page, thus overriding the global style.css\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"wp_customcss\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"textarea\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:39;a:2:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"General Settings\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"heading\";}i:40;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:49:\"Contact form Shortcode (for listing detail pages)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:88:\"Contact Form 7 Plugin shortcode for the simple contact form on each listing detail page.\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"wp_contactshortcode\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:41;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:44:\"Contact form Shortcode (for Contact Us page)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:136:\"Contact Form 7 Plugin shortcode for the Contact Us page. To create this page, create a new Page, and choose the \'Contact\' Page Template.\";s:2:\"id\";s:25:\"wp_contactuspageshortcode\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:42;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:27:\"Google Map of your location\";s:4:\"desc\";s:105:\"Full address, city state, and zip/postal code, etc for your location.  To be used in the Contact Us page.\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_contactmap\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:43;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:30:\"Blog posts per page (homepage)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:145:\"If you are showing blog posts on the homepage, how many do you want to show? (note: layout is 4 items per row, so multiples of 4 is a good idea.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"wp_blognumber\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"6\";}i:44;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Compare Page\";s:4:\"desc\";s:187:\"Your \'Compare\' listings page.  (Note: you must create a \'Page\' for Compare. Give it a title. Also give it the Page Template name called \'Compare\'. That page will appear in this dropdown.)\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"wp_comparepage\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:10:{i:0;s:14:\"Select a page:\";i:1;s:7:\"Compare\";i:2;s:10:\"Contact Us\";i:3;s:14:\"Meet the Staff\";i:4;s:26:\"Purchase: Lets get started\";i:5;s:11:\"Sample Page\";i:6;s:14:\"Search Results\";i:7;s:8:\"Site Map\";i:8;s:4:\"Sold\";i:9;s:10:\"Thank You!\";}s:3:\"std\";s:0:\"\";}i:45;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:35:\"Recent Listings Quantity (homepage)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:118:\"How many recent listings do you want to show in the homepage? (this is the thumbnail image version of Recent Listings)\";s:2:\"id\";s:28:\"wp_recentlistingsnumber_home\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:3:\"std\";s:1:\"3\";}i:46;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:14:\"Banner choices\";s:4:\"desc\";s:611:\"Enter all possible banner choices. One banner per line.<br /><br />Optionally set a color for any banner. To do this, enter the \'pipe\' character (|) and then the color. The color can be either a HEX value or English word, like \'Blue\', \'Red\', etc.<br /><br />Example:<br /><br />Sold|red<br />Reduced|#FFFFFF<br />Pending|Yellow<br /><br />Note: If you change the color for a banner, you must re-choose the banner from each listing and re-publish.<br /><br />If you choose 2 banner choices, the color is always taken from the first banner choice.<br /><br />Note: Banners cannot be translated to other languages.\";s:2:\"id\";s:9:\"wp_banner\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"textarea\";s:3:\"std\";s:29:\"Reduced\nSold\nPending\nReserved\";}i:47;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:23:\"Service History choices\";s:4:\"desc\";s:189:\"Enter all possible service history choices. One per line. These will be a choice to pick when you add/edit a listing.<br /><br />Note: These choices cannot be translated to other languages.\";s:2:\"id\";s:17:\"wp_servicehistory\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"textarea\";s:3:\"std\";s:135:\"Full Service History\nMain Dealer Service History\nPart Service History\nPart Main Dealer History\nFirst Service Not Due\nNo Service History\";}i:48;a:5:{s:4:\"name\";s:29:\"Value Added Tax choices (VAT)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:288:\"Enter all possible Value Added Tax choices. One per line. These will be a choice to pick when you add/edit a listing. (This is most often used for car dealer sites outside of the U.S.)<br /><br />This text can be translated to other languages by appending your text in |en, |de, |es, etc.\";s:2:\"id\";s:6:\"wp_vat\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"textarea\";s:3:\"std\";s:29:\"+VAT\nVAT Exempt\nIncluding VAT\";}i:49;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:13:\"First Feature\";s:4:\"desc\";s:124:\"The slideshow, latest listings, and search results show 3 features separated by a vertical line.  This is the first feature.\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"wp_firstfeature\";s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"select\";s:7:\"options\";a:6:{i:0;s:7:\"Mileage\";i:1;s:12:\"Transmission\";i:2;s:9:\"Fuel Type\";i:3;s:11:\"Engine Size\";i:4;s:9:\"Body Type\";i:5;s:4:\"Year\";}s:3:\"std\";s:7:\"Mileage\";}